data.title: Cardano (ADA) under pressure as whales dump 100M tokens, leading to price decline and lower trading volumes. Hopes for a rebound with ETF approvals and network enhancements.
data.description: The cryptocurrency Cardano (ADA) is facing increased selling pressure from large investors, leading to a decrease in its price. Trading volumes for ADA have also been slowing down. Experts are optimistic for a potential recovery driven by the approval of Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs) and enhancements to the network.

data.title: Tech futures up after Meta-led dip, Amazon & Apple earnings shine. Positive trend after drop, reflecting investor optimism.
data.description: Stock futures in the technology sector experienced a rise driven by positive earnings reports from major companies like Amazon and Apple, following a market decline led by Meta. The Dow Jones Futures saw an increase as tech giants' performances boosted investor confidence after a recent downturn. This shift comes after Meta's leading role in a market slide, indicating a potential turnaround in the market sentiment. This update showcases the impact of strong earnings results on key players like Amazon and Apple on the overall market dynamics.

data.title: First International Jewelry Fashion Theme Month starts in Shanghai, with 2025 Shanghai Haute Couture Week, held in Grand Yuyuan Cultural Area on October 30, 2025.
data.description: In the vibrant city of Hong Kong on October 30, 2025, the Grand Yuyuan Cultural Area marked the commencement of the First International Jewelry Fashion Theme Month and the highly anticipated 2025 Shanghai Haute Couture Week. This celebration, which follows the recent establishment of the Shanghai, sets the stage for a month-long showcase of exquisite jewelry designs and cutting-edge fashion. Stay tuned for updates on this glamorous event that brings together fashion lovers and trendsetters from across the globe.

data.title: Sen. Elizabeth Warren criticizes Trump's plan to introduce crypto to 401(k) plans, deeming it risky for Americans' savings.
data.description: Senator Elizabeth Warren (D-Mass.) expressed concerns about President Donald Trump's recent executive orders enabling cryptocurrencies in 401(k) plans. She warned that this decision could jeopardize the hard-earned savings of Americans, labeling the crypto market as "shadowy" and lacking proper protection measures. Warren emphasized the importance of safeguarding individuals' retirement funds from risky investments pushed by Wall Street. Trump's initiative to introduce private equity and crypto into 401(k) accounts raises apprehensions about the security of these investments. Warren urged for stricter regulations to protect Americans from potential financial risks associated with these alternative assets.

data.title: Iozera acquires 4.5MW data center in Houston, plans to expand to 10MW AI hub in a network of AI factories.
data.description: In Houston, Texas, on October 30, 2025, Iozera announced it's acquiring a 4.5-megawatt data center that will be upgraded to a 10-megawatt, AI-ready multi-tenant hub. This center marks the beginning of a series of AI factories planned by the company.

data.title: 4DMT partners with Otsuka Pharma to develop 4D-150 for wet AMD & DME in Asia-Pacific region, incl. Japan.
data.description: Emeryville, California - On October 30, 2025, 4D Molecular Therapeutics (Nasdaq: FDMT, 4DMT) disclosed a significant strategic alliance with Otsuka Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd. (Otsuka). This partnership aims to collaborate on the development and distribution of 4D-150, a potential treatment for wet age-related macular degeneration (wet AMD) and diabetic macular edema (DME) in the larger Asia-Pacific (APAC) area, which includes Japan. 4D-150 holds promise to revolutionize treatment approaches and deliver substantial advantages to patients. This move signifies a notable milestone for both companies in the biotechnology sector.
